# Telegram Bot Rules

## Role
Telegram bot is a thin adapter layer between Telegram and backend API.

## Hard constraints
- NEVER access database directly
- NEVER import backend internal modules (db/, services/, routers/)
- ONLY communicate with backend via HTTP API
- Bot must contain NO business logic (no analysis, no AI, no scoring)

## Responsibilities
- Receive user messages from Telegram
- Send user input to backend API
- Return backend responses to user
- Handle basic command routing (/start, /help)

## Architecture
Telegram → Bot (aiogram) → HTTP → FastAPI backend → DB

## Message handling rules
- Any user message is treated as raw input (dream text)
- Bot does not interpret meaning of dreams
- Bot does not classify or analyze content

## HTTP client rules
- Use a dedicated backend_client module
- All API calls must be async (httpx or equivalent)

## Anti-patterns (forbidden)
- ❌ embedding prompts in bot logic
- ❌ calling LLM from bot
- ❌ storing state in bot memory
- ❌ duplicating backend logic

## Goal
Bot must remain replaceable without changing core system.